You need to style the “overlay” part of the Dialog component.

```css
vaadin-dialog-overlay::part(overlay) {
  border: 2px solid red;
}
```

See the documentation for some more info: https://vaadin.com/docs/latest/styling/getting-started/#styling.get-started.sub-component-styling


As a side note, you should also make sure you&#39;re applying the dark theme to the `&lt;html theme=&quot;dark&quot;&gt;` element, instead of `&lt;body theme=&quot;dark&quot;&gt;`. When you set the attribute on the `&lt;body&gt;` element, the shadow colors are not updated correctly, and that makes the contrast between the overlay elements and the main background less apparent.

Seems like the issue is related to fact that in SpringConfig-servlet.xml you have:
```
&lt;property name=&quot;prefix&quot; value=&quot;/WEB-INF/views/&quot;/&gt;
```
but views are located in `webapp/views`.&lt;br&gt;
You can try moving them to `/WEB-INF/views/` folder.

